\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Binary data matrix (BDM)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
BDM file format is a tab delimited binary matrix of items (i.e.
 genes) and conditions.
 1 indicates that the item has this condition or is in this gene set and
 0 otherwise.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename images/format_BDM.png
	lyxscale 20

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Gene matrix transposed (GMT)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
GMT file format is a simple tab delimited file to provide gene sets.
 Each row describes a gene set, the first column indicates the name of the
 gene set and the second column the description.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename images/format_GMT.png
	lyxscale 20

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
GMT files provided as Data in GiTools will be converted to Binary Data Matrices
 in which each gene set will be a column (i.e.
 condition) and each gene (or item) will have a value of 1 if it was in
 the gene set and 0 otherwise.
\end_layout

