\begin_layout Subsection
Two columns mapping (TCM)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
TCM file format is a simple tab delimited file in which the first column
 indicates the ID of gene or item and the second column the name of the
 module it belongs to.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename images/format_TCM.png
	lyxscale 30

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Annotations
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The format of annotations files is a simple table in which the first column
 is the ID used in the matrix or module file and next columns are annotations
 of these items.
 The first row is the header of the columns.
\end_layout

